HEADWORD: Firewarden
<hw>Fire"ward`en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An officer who
has authority to direct in the extinguishing of fires, or to order what
precautions shall be taken against fires; -- called also
<altname>fireward</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

